###Reject vs. fail to reject $\text{H}_0$

$\begin{align}
&\text{P-value }< \alpha \rightarrow \text{reject } \text{H}_0 \rightarrow \text{accept } \text{H}_\text{a} \\
&\text{P-value } \geq \alpha \rightarrow \text{fail to reject } \text{H}_0 \rightarrow \text{cannot accept } \text{H}_\text{a}
\end{align}$

In this test, the null hypothesis is that there is not a linear relationship between the two variables, or, $\text{H}_0\text{: } \beta=0$ (where $\beta$ is the population slope). The alternative hypothesis is that there is a linear relationship, or, $\text{H}_\text{a}\text{: }\beta \neq 0$.

